RECOMMENDATION
4 FOR
HOUSE BILL NO. 4486 By: Townley
5
6
7 POLICY COMMITTEE RECOMMENDATION
8 An Act relating to the State Capitol Preservation
Commission; authorizing the placement of a monument
9 near the State Capitol Arch; directing the State
Capitol Commission to work with private entities to
10 erect the monument; providing for codification; and
providing an effective date.
11
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 4110.2 of Title 74, unless there
17 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 The State Capitol Preservation Commission or designee is hereby
19 authorized to permit and arrange for the placement of the Gold Star
20 Family Monument. This monument shall be designed, constructed, and
21 placed on the Capitol Grounds by private entities at no expense to
22 the State of Oklahoma. The State Capitol Preservation Commission or
23 designee is authorized to assist private entities in placing the
24
Req. No. 16531 Page 1

1 monu ment in the northwest corner behind the State Capitol Arch for
2 the monument and arranging a suitable time for its placement.
3 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
